'''''Darkwell''''', by [[Douglas Niles]], is the third book in the [[Moonshae trilogy]]. Niles would later continue the story in the [[Druidhome trilogy]].

{{quote|''The ultimate struggle of good and evil...''

''[[Tristan Kendrick|Tristan]], new-crowned king of the [[Ffolk]], and [[Robyn Moonsinger|Robyn]] the druid must confront an [[Bhaal|evil]] that threatens their beloved [[Moonshae Isles]]. But they must also resolve their own relationship—and decide if they will rule as king and queen or live forever as bitter enemies.''}}
